ttv-split 0.4.0
Split dataset into two or more files for test/train/validation sets

USAGE:
    ttv split [FLAGS] [OPTIONS] <input> --prop <prop>... --rows <rows>...

FLAGS:
    -C, --compressed-output    Compress output files using gzip
        --csv                  Parse input as CSV. Only needed if rows contain embedded newlines - will impact
                               performance.
    -d, --decompress-input     Decompress input from gzip format
    -h, --help                 Prints help information
    -n, --no-header            Don't treat the first row as a header
    -V, --version              Prints version information

OPTIONS:
    -c, --chunk-size <chunk-size>          Maximum number of rows per output chunk
    -o, --output-prefix <output-prefix>    Output filename prefix. Only used if reading from stdin
    -p, --prop <prop>...                   Specify splits by proportion of rows
    -r, --rows <rows>...                   Specify splits by number of rows
    -s, --seed <seed>                      RNG seed, for reproducibility
    -t, --total-rows <total-rows>          Number of rows in input file. Used for progress when using proportion splits

ARGS:
    <input>    Data to split, optionally gzip compressed. If '-', read from stdin
